<fr:p>This is, I suppose, something of an exaltation of larks, and I'm reminded of my copy of <fr:link
type="local"
href="jameslipton.xml"
addr="jameslipton"
title="James Lipton">James Lipton</fr:link>'s <fr:link
type="local"
href="lipton-an-exaltation-of-larks.xml"
addr="lipton-an-exaltation-of-larks"
title="An Exaltation of Larks">book</fr:link> (it must be somewhere in the boxes). It seems to me good sense to take 
  <html:img
xmlns:html="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml"
src="zzhaoe-000Y/murder.svg"
style="width: 1em" />
 (a quadriplication of 
  
  <html:span
xmlns:html="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml"
lang="ja">烏</html:span>

, "crow") to mean a murder of crows, and to extend this principle to any other noun.</fr:p></fr:mainmatter><fr:backmatter /></fr:tree></fr:mainmatter><fr:backmatter /></fr:tree></fr:backmatter></fr:tree>